Enum Class AcceptRequestTypes

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<AcceptRequestTypes>
grafioschtrader.gtnet.AcceptRequestTypes
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<AcceptRequestTypes>, Constable
public enum AcceptRequestTypes extends Enum<AcceptRequestTypes>
Defines the acceptance modes for incoming GTNet data exchange requests. Each GTNetEntity can be configured with one of these acceptance types to control how the local instance responds to data queries from remote instances:
  • AC_CLOSED - No requests accepted, data exchange disabled
  • AC_OPEN - Accepts incoming requests, provides data to remote instances
  • AC_PUSH_OPEN - Accepts requests AND actively receives pushed updates from remote instances. This mode is only available for GTNetExchangeKindType.LAST_PRICE as these instances maintain more active connections with more current data.
Note: AC_PUSH_OPEN is preferred for data exchange because instances in this mode typically have more active connections and therefore more and newer data available.
See Also:
  • GTNetExchangeKindType.LAST_PRICE
